# AI-Powered Documentation System Project Plan 

This plan outlines the overall goal, key objectives for each phase, and the gating items necessary to progress from one phase to the next. This document will help guide the development process, ensure all team members are aligned, and facilitate tracking progress against milestones.

This project plan will be iteratively reviewed and adjusted as needed to align with project realities and stakeholder feedback. 

# Project Goal

To enhance the efficiency, consistency, and scalability of documentation processes for Sage product by integrating AI capabilities into the existing content creation workflow, enabling automated drafting, retrieval, modification, and review of content.

## Overview of Phases

1. **Phase 1: Foundation and Initial Integration**

   * **Objective**:   
     Establish core AI functionalities (Retrieval, Drafting, Review agents) (1A).   
     Integrate these with MadCap Flare through a custom toolbar. (1B)

   * **Key Deliverables**:  
     * Query and Response agent to interact with the users and other agents  
     * Orchestration Agent to control activities an ensure responses are properly executed and returned  
     * Retrieval Agents setup for JIRA and Confluence.  
     * Drafting Agent integration with OpenAI's LLM APIs.  
     * Initial Review Agent for assessing AI-generated content.  
     * Basic Flare Toolbar customization for AI interaction. (1B)

   * **Gating Items to Phase 2**:  
     * Successful integration and basic functionality tests of all agents.  
     * Positive initial feedback from user acceptance testing with technical writers.  
     * Establishment of security protocols and compliance checks.  
         
2. **Phase 2: Enhancement and Expansion**

   * **Objective**: Enhance AI capabilities with advanced natural language processing and machine learning techniques, expand the scope of automation across more documentation types, and improve the user interface for greater ease of use.

   * **Key Deliverables**:  
     * Advanced features for the Review Agent, including deeper content analysis and style consistency checks.  
     * Expansion of the Drafting Agent's capabilities to handle more complex document structures.  
     * Enhanced user interface in Flare Toolbar, incorporating more feedback mechanisms and customization options.

   * **Gating Items to Phase 3**:  
     * Demonstrated improvement in content quality and reduction in manual interventions.  
     * Successful deployment and operation of enhanced features in a production environment.  
     * Detailed user feedback and revision cycles to refine AI outputs.  
         
3. **Phase 3: Optimization and Full-Scale Deployment**

   * **Objective**: Optimize the system for high efficiency, scale up the solution to cover documentation needs across the organization, and automate the documentation lifecycle where feasible.

   * **Key Deliverables**:  
     * Full integration of the AI system with the organization’s content management systems.  
     * Training programs and support structures for all documentation staff.  
     * Learning and adaptation mechanisms for AI models to improve over time based on feedback.

   * **Gating Items to Completion**:  
     * Achieving targeted performance metrics such as reduction in drafting time and improvements in content accuracy.  
     * High user adoption rates and positive feedback across departments.  
     * Establishment of a continuous improvement framework for future enhancements.

#### **Evaluation Metrics Across Phases**

* **Performance Improvements**: Measurable reductions in manual drafting and review time, as well as improvements in handling document revisions and updates.

* **Content Quality**: Measurable improvements to the accuracy and consistency of AI-generated content, as well as the reduction in error rates post-review.

* **User Satisfaction**: Comprehensive feedback from all user groups to assess the impact on their workflow and overall satisfaction with the system.

This overarching project plan sets a clear trajectory for the integration and scaling of AI within your documentation processes, with distinct objectives and deliverables for each phase that build upon the successes of the previous stages. 

## 

## Phase 1 of the AI-powered Documentation System 

#### **Phase 1 Overview**

* **Objective**: To integrate AI agents into the existing documentation workflow to automate the drafting, retrieval, and review of content, thus enhancing productivity and consistency.  
* **Scope**:  
  * Development of Retrieval, Drafting, and Review agents.  
  * Integration with MadCap Flare through a custom toolbar.  
  * Use of OpenAI's LLM APIs for content generation and review.  
  * Setup of an in-memory data store for efficient data management.  
  * Security and API management setup for secure and efficient operations.

#### **Architectural Diagram**

![][image1]

### **Description of System Agents**

![][image2]

* #### **Query and Response Agent:**

  * #### **Function:** Interacts with users to receive queries and provide responses. Acts as the interface between the user and the backend AI processes.

  * #### **Orchestration Agent:**

    * #### **Function:** Manages and coordinates the activities of various AI agents, ensuring that tasks are executed efficiently and responses are accurately returned to the Query and Response Agent.

  * #### **Retrieval Agents:**

    * #### **Function:** Responsible for fetching necessary data from JIRA and Confluence. These agents query the APIs based on input from the Query and Response Agent and provide the gathered data to the Drafting Agent.

  * #### **Drafting Agent:**

    * #### **Function:** Uses the data retrieved by the Retrieval Agents to generate content drafts. This agent integrates with OpenAI's LLM APIs to produce structured drafts based on the input data.

  * #### **Review Agent:**

    * #### **Function:** Assesses the AI-generated content for quality, accuracy, and adherence to style guidelines. Provides feedback and suggestions for improvements to the Drafting Agent.

### **Expected API Interactions**

This sequence diagram reflects the step-by-step API interactions and data flow among the agents and external services.

* The `Query and Response Agent` initiates the process by sending queries to the `Orchestration Agent`.  
* The `Orchestration Agent` delegates tasks to the `Retrieval Agents` which interact with JIRA and Confluence to fetch required data.  
* Retrieved data is passed back up the chain to eventually be processed into drafts by the `Drafting Agent` using OpenAI's LLM APIs.  
* Drafts are reviewed by the `Review Agent`, and the finalized content is sent back through the `Orchestration Agent` to the `Query and Response Agent`, which displays the results on the Flare Toolbar.

![][image3]

### **Expected Technologies**

1. #### **Programming Languages and Frameworks:** 

   * #### **Python:** Primary language for backend development, used for scripting and automation of AI functionalities.

   * #### **JavaScript:** Used for developing the custom toolbar in MadCap Flare and handling frontend interactions. 

2. #### **APIs and Integrations:** 

   * #### **OpenAI LLM APIs:** For leveraging advanced language models to generate and review content.

   * #### **JIRA API:** For retrieving data related to project management and software development tasks.

   * #### **Confluence API:** For accessing documentation and collaborative content stored in Confluence. 

3. #### **Database and Data Management:** 

   * #### **Redis:** An in-memory database to facilitate rapid data retrieval and caching, enhancing the responsiveness of the system. 

4. #### **Development Tools and Platforms:** 

   * #### **GitHub:** For version control and management of the development process.

   * #### **Docker/Containerization:** For creating a consistent development environment that can be easily replicated and deployed.

   * #### **Flask/Django:** For setting up a lightweight web server that facilitates communication between the Flare toolbar and the backend Python services. 

5. #### **Security Technologies:** 

   * #### **OAuth:** For secure API authentication and authorization.

   * #### **SSL/TLS:** For ensuring secure data transmission between the system components and external APIs. 

6. #### **Monitoring and Operations:** 

   * #### **Prometheus/Grafana:** For monitoring system performance and health.

   * #### **ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana):** For logging and analyzing system logs to troubleshoot and optimize operations.

### **Agents**

Agents will be built using current standards for Agentic AI platforms. Tool agents will be supplied with the SDK/API guide for the connected platform and what specific fields to utilize and calls to make to retrieve information.

The Retrieval Agent is skilled in accessing structured data from software development tools like JIRA and Confluence. **Background:** This agent leverages advanced data fetching technologies to ensure that all necessary information for content generation and review is accurate and up-to-date. Its design focuses on minimizing response time and maximizing data relevancy, adapting seamlessly to various data environments. **Goal:** To automate and optimize the retrieval of project management and documentation data to facilitate quicker drafting and review processes. **Tasks:** Connect securely to JIRA and Confluence APIs to fetch the latest updates and documents. Filter and prioritize data based on project needs and predefined criteria. Provide a summarized dataset to the Drafting Agent for content generation. Only fetch data relevant to active documentation projects to avoid data overload. **Other Instructions:** Maintain a log of all data requests and responses for troubleshooting and optimization. Continuously update the data fetching algorithms based on new requirements from the documentation team. Collaborate with the Orchestration Agent to schedule and prioritize data retrieval tasks. Stay up-to-date on the latest API changes and updates from JIRA and Confluence.  |

### **Flare Integration (1B)**

The system should function before Flare integration is attempted. A custom Toolbar in Flare will allow natural interaction by Information Developers. The back end will also therefore support integration into other applications. This approach enables support for other content types, application interfaces, and scaling across more teams.

| ![][image4] | Flare Toolbar: This is the central hub in the UI where users interact with AI features. The toolbar would ideally include: Button "Fetch Data": Initiates a retrieval request to the AI system to fetch necessary data. Button "Generate Draft": Requests the AI to create a draft based on the retrieved or specified data. Button "Review Content": Sends the draft for AI-driven review to ensure quality and compliance. Display Area: Shows the results of AI processes or any feedback from the AI system. User: Represents the end-user interacting with the Flare Toolbar, performing tasks, and viewing results. AI System: Handles tasks requested by the toolbar and returns results or feedback.  |

## Phase 2 of the AI-powered Documentation System 

Phase 2 will take on additional requirements based on Phase 1 implementation and user feedback.

#### **Phase 2: Enhancement and Expansion**

* **Objective**: Expand AI capabilities to enhance content accuracy, handle more complex documentation structures, and improve the user interface for easier interaction.

* **Key Deliverables**:  
  * Create and populate a vector DB of existing content to improve the context understanding and generation capabilities of the AI.  
  * Fine-Tune LLM model on current documentation content.  
  * Develop an intent profiler Agent to ensure the system is being used for its intended purpose.  
  * Develop a more sophisticated Review Agent that can handle nuanced language and style variations.  
  * Introduce additional UI components in the Flare Toolbar to allow more detailed user interactions and feedback.  
  * Analysis of potential improvements and impact of inclusion of Knowledge graphs in the retrieval and generation processes (GRAG/GRAR) through static or dynamically created Knowledge Graph Structures.

* **Technologies to be introduced**:  
  * Vector Database with existing high quality content,  
  * Interactions with terminology management system,   
  * Advanced routing to seamlessly blend AI functionalities within the Flare environment.

* **Milestones**:  
  * Development of advanced AI features.  
  * Beta testing with end users to gather initial feedback and iterate on UI improvements.  
  * Full system integration test.

* **Gating Items to Phase 3**:  
  * Verification of enhanced AI performance against set benchmarks.  
  * Positive feedback from beta testing indicating readiness for wider deployment.  
  * Decision on incorporation of Knowledge Graphs into the Phase 3 deliverables.

## Phase 3 of the AI-powered Documentation System 

Phase 3 will take on additional requirements based on Phase 1&2 implementation and user feedback

#### **Phase 3: Optimization and Full-Scale Deployment**

* **Objective**: Optimize the system for organizational-wide deployment, ensuring scalability, robustness, and user-friendliness.

* **Key Deliverables**:  
  * Advanced Agentic frameworks and libraries (e.g., GRAG/GRAR) for deeper learning capabilities and enhanced GenAI output.  
  * Full integration of the AI system with the organization’s broader content management systems.  
  * Comprehensive training programs for all relevant staff members.  
  * Establishment of a continuous learning framework for the AI to adapt to new data and user feedback.

* **Technologies to be introduced**:  
  * Scalable cloud services for handling increased data load and storage.  
  * Advanced analytics tools to monitor system performance and user engagement.

* **Milestones**:  
  * Deployment across all documentation teams.  
  * Final system-wide optimization tweaks.  
  * Launch of a continuous improvement program based on AI learnings and user feedback.

* **Gating Items to Project Completion**:  
  * Achievement of system stability and performance metrics.  
  * High user adoption rates and satisfaction across all teams.
